<li><a href="http://www.nuclearfiles.org/menu/key-issues/nuclear-weapons/issues/proliferation/index.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.nuclearfiles.org/menu/key-issues/nuclear-weapons/issues/proliferation/index.htm" rel="nofollow">Nuclear Files.org</a> Comprehensive information regarding nuclear proliferation, including case studies.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.nuclearfiles.org/menu/key-issues/nuclear-weapons/issues/terrorism/director-general-threat-of-nuclear-terrorism.html" class="external text" title="http://www.nuclearfiles.org/menu/key-issues/nuclear-weapons/issues/terrorism/director-general-threat-of-nuclear-terrorism.html" rel="nofollow">Nuclear Files.org</a> Nuclear Proliferation and the Potential Threat of Nuclear Terrorism</li>
<li><a href="http://www.fas.org/sgp/crs/nuke/RL31559.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.fas.org/sgp/crs/nuke/RL31559.pdf" rel="nofollow">Proliferation Control Regimes: Background and Status</a> Congressional Research Service Report, December 26, 2006.</li>
<li>George Perkovich, <a href="http://www.ifri.org/files/Securite_defense/Perkovich_Reforming_Nuclear_Order.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.ifri.org/files/Securite_defense/Perkovich_Reforming_Nuclear_Order.pdf" rel="nofollow">"Principles for Reforming the Nuclear Order"</a>, <i>Proliferation Papers</i>, Paris, Ifri, Fall 2008</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Jamyang_Norbu" title="Jamyang Norbu">Jamyang Norbu</a>, <a href="http://www.phayul.com/news/article.aspx?id=23872&amp;article=THE+CHINA+(PROLIFERATION)+SYNDROME+-+Jamyang+Norbu" class="external text" title="http://www.phayul.com/news/article.aspx?id=23872&amp;article=THE+CHINA+(PROLIFERATION)+SYNDROME+-+Jamyang+Norbu" rel="nofollow">The China (Proliferation) Syndrome</a>, <i><a href="/wiki/Phayul.com" title="Phayul.com">Phayul.com</a></i>, February 20, 2009.</li>
</ul>
